President Muhammadu Buhari has expressed his deep condolences to the Abubakar family over the death of Engineer Usman Abubakar, chairman of the Board of the Nigeria Railway Corporation (NRC). According to a statement by his senior special assistant on media, Garba Shehu, President Buhari said he would personally miss the wise counsel of Abubakar, describing the deceased as a well-educated and dignified gentleman. “Our thoughts and prayers are with his family, the government and people of Katsina State following the irreparable loss of this selfless and patriotic Nigerian,” he said. The president, who was represented at the burial of his close associate yesterday at the National Mosque in Abuja by his chief of staff, Abba Kyari, and a number of presidency officials, prayed to Allah to grant him Jannatul Firdaus  The late Abubakar, who was buried at Gudu District Cemetery in Abuja amidst tears by family, friends and well-wishers, died at the age of 68 after a brief illness in Abuja. He hailed from Sandamu Local Government Area of Katsina State. Abubakar served as commissioner of works in Katsina State in 1987, and was chairman of Daura Tannery, Interlinked Technologies and Jebba Paper Mills. He was appointed chairman of NRC by President Muhammadu Buhari on September 27, 2016. The funeral, conducted in accordance with Islamic rites, was attended by the Minister of Water Resources, Suleiman Adamu; managing director of NRC, Freeborn Okhiria and other sympathisers. The deceased is survived by a wife, Hajiya Rabi Sule-Maiyawo, and three children , Lawal, Buhari and Mustapha.